¶ I'm fresh off the boat ¶

01:33.260 --> 01:34.927
Eddie's birthday is next week.

01:34.929 --> 01:37.129
It's time to start repairing
the decorations.

01:37.131 --> 01:40.766
Mm, I think it's finally time
we send him

01:40.768 --> 01:42.568
to the big fiesta in the sky.

01:42.570 --> 01:44.937
Okay, I'll rip the head off
and use it as a planter.

01:44.939 --> 01:46.605
[ Door closes ]
[ Sighs ]

01:46.607 --> 01:49.241
Well, here I am,
home from Trent's early.

01:49.243 --> 01:50.809
All the other guys
are still there,

01:50.811 --> 01:52.945
unrolling their sleeping bags,
but not me.

01:52.947 --> 01:54.713
Because my mom won't let me do

01:54.715 --> 01:56.615
the sleepover part
of a sleepover.

01:56.617 --> 01:59.618
You will thank me
when you don't get pedophiled.

01:59.620 --> 02:03.088
Are those
the birthday-party decorations?

02:03.090 --> 02:04.556
I wanted to talk to you guys
about that.

02:04.558 --> 02:06.291
I bet you did.

02:06.293 --> 02:07.759
Just because we're living
in the suburbs now

02:07.761 --> 02:10.629
doesn't mean you get
some big, fancy birthday party.

02:10.631 --> 02:13.398
No bowling alleys,
no pizza parties with a rat.

02:13.400 --> 02:15.334
Please.

02:15.336 --> 02:18.137
¶¶

02:21.942 --> 02:23.142
I don't want a party this year.

02:23.144 --> 02:25.110
Really? What?

02:25.112 --> 02:27.913
I'm turning 12.
I'm almost a teenager.

02:27.915 --> 02:30.816
I just want to have
a chill, regular day,

02:30.818 --> 02:31.917
hang out with my friends
at the mall.

02:31.919 --> 02:33.652
So no party at all?

02:33.654 --> 02:35.187
No party.

02:35.189 --> 02:37.523
No cake?
No singing?
No presents?

02:37.525 --> 02:41.293
Yes presents... cash only,
but I will accept gold.

02:41.295 --> 02:42.794
Respect.

02:42.796 --> 02:44.596
You don't even want
birthday noodles?

02:44.598 --> 02:45.598
It's okay, mom.

02:45.599 --> 02:47.132
I know they take you so long
to make.

02:47.134 --> 02:48.567
No need to do anything special.

02:49.803 --> 02:51.436
Okay.
If that's what you want.

02:51.438 --> 02:52.671
It is.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.673
I'm glad we did this.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.510
Thank you.

03:00.047 --> 03:02.047
So, how do we feel about this?

03:02.049 --> 03:04.316
I guess if he doesn't want
a party...

03:04.318 --> 03:08.153
It does save me
a trip to piñata town.

03:08.155 --> 03:09.655
And we'll have a free Saturday.

03:09.657 --> 03:11.323
We can go to work.

03:11.325 --> 03:13.659
I haven't gotten to work
on a Saturday in years!

03:13.661 --> 03:17.029
¶¶

03:17.031 --> 03:18.463
[ birds chirping ]

03:18.465 --> 03:20.098
Both: It's today!

03:22.369 --> 03:24.970
Let's carry Eddie's present
down together.

03:32.746 --> 03:35.647
Happy birthday...

03:36.650 --> 03:37.983
Thanks, man.
Is that cash?

03:37.985 --> 03:41.186
Where are all the streamers
and scallion pancakes

03:41.188 --> 03:42.487
and birthday hats?

03:42.489 --> 03:43.755
We're not doing
a party this year.

03:43.757 --> 03:45.424
Eddie said he didn't want one.

03:45.426 --> 03:47.893
So we're just gonna let him
be 11 forever?

03:47.895 --> 03:49.561
That's not how it works.
You know that, right?

03:49.563 --> 03:51.163
Aah!

03:51.165 --> 03:54.066
[ Speaks Spanish ]

03:55.502 --> 03:56.868
Why didn't you tell us
there was no party?

03:56.870 --> 03:58.036
Because we're your parents.

03:58.038 --> 03:59.671
We don't have to tell you
things.

03:59.673 --> 04:01.773
You have to tell us things.
Plus, I forgot.

04:03.177 --> 04:05.944
I'm gonna head to the mall.
See you, guys.

04:05.946 --> 04:07.879
Remember, no gyros
from the food court.

04:07.881 --> 04:09.448
I don't trust meat
without bones.

04:10.618 --> 04:12.784
Well, I'm gonna head to work.

04:12.786 --> 04:14.219
Mitch called in sick,

04:14.221 --> 04:16.722
and Nancy refuses
to marry the ketchups...

04:16.724 --> 04:18.957
Because of her religion.

04:20.561 --> 04:23.795
¶¶

04:23.797 --> 04:27.466
[ sniffing ]

04:27.468 --> 04:29.268
I don't smell any poison.

04:29.270 --> 04:31.370
The termite guy said
we wouldn't smell anything.

04:31.372 --> 04:34.373
An odorless gas for a bug
you can't see?

04:34.375 --> 04:35.874
Smart scam.

04:35.876 --> 04:37.976
I thought
you weren't gonna come today

04:37.978 --> 04:40.245
because you were busy
celebrating Eddie's birthday.

04:40.247 --> 04:42.281
Eddie said he didn't want
a birthday party this year.

04:42.283 --> 04:45.117
Jessica.

04:45.119 --> 04:47.386
Do you really think Eddie
doesn't want a party?

04:47.388 --> 04:49.755
That's what he said.

04:49.757 --> 04:52.557
Last year, Nicole said that
she wanted to eat tater tots

04:52.559 --> 04:54.159
and watch TV for her birthday.

04:54.161 --> 04:58.130
So that's what we did,
and she cried for a week.

04:58.132 --> 04:59.498
Oh.
Uh-huh.

04:59.500 --> 05:02.634
So, this year,
I showed up with horses,

05:02.636 --> 05:05.370
and we rode them
to the olive garden.

05:10.344 --> 05:13.945
Oh, quick, Jessica, grab onto me
before I float away!

05:13.947 --> 05:16.148
Just let go of a few!

05:16.150 --> 05:18.150
You're in control!
They are not in control!

05:18.152 --> 05:20.419
No, no, it's...
I... I was just joking.

05:20.421 --> 05:22.788
[ Sighs ] I wouldn't joke
about that, Louis.

05:22.790 --> 05:25.457
I saw that happen to a French
boy in a documentary.

05:25.459 --> 05:26.858
Flew right into the sun.

05:28.262 --> 05:29.861
Come on.
Let's go find Eddie.

05:29.863 --> 05:32.097
To be honest,
I was a little disappointed

05:32.099 --> 05:34.032
he didn't want
to celebrate his birthday.

05:34.034 --> 05:36.201
I miss how serious he looks
when he makes a wish.

05:36.203 --> 05:39.271
It is special
when he concentrates.

05:39.273 --> 05:41.139
So, we'll go in, we'll find
Eddie and his friends,

05:41.141 --> 05:42.641
pick up a cake,
go to piñata town,

05:42.643 --> 05:43.875
then we'll all go home,

05:43.877 --> 05:45.610
and I'll make everybody
birthday noodles.

05:45.612 --> 05:47.379
For our new piñata,

05:47.381 --> 05:49.581
I'm thinking frog
with some kind of a hat.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.387
[ Gasps ] Look!
There they are.

05:55.389 --> 05:57.022
[ Laughter ]

06:01.829 --> 06:04.129
Are those party hats?

06:04.131 --> 06:05.430
I don't think so.

06:07.334 --> 06:09.401
Is that a birthday cake?

06:09.403 --> 06:10.869
I don't think so.

06:12.873 --> 06:17.409
Louis, his friends threw him
a surprise birthday party.

06:17.411 --> 06:19.211
[ Glass clinking ]

06:19.213 --> 06:20.579
I'd like to thank you all

06:20.581 --> 06:23.081
for rsvp'ing to my birthday
party in a timely manner

06:23.083 --> 06:25.417
so that way,
I could secure the patio.

06:25.419 --> 06:27.386
Yeah!
Whoo!

06:27.388 --> 06:31.022
Um, I guess he just wanted
to celebrate with his friends.

06:31.024 --> 06:32.157
No adults.

06:32.159 --> 06:33.159
What's up?!
What's up?!

06:33.160 --> 06:34.426
Hey!

06:34.428 --> 06:36.828
Mitch, you came!

06:36.830 --> 06:38.363
I wouldn't miss
your dirty dozen.

06:38.365 --> 06:40.265
You ask for Mitch,
you get Mitch!

06:40.267 --> 06:42.067
All right!

06:42.069 --> 06:43.969
Yeah!
Let's get this party started!

06:50.010 --> 06:52.210
You know, I've been thinking,

06:52.212 --> 06:54.913
we're such good kids that
mom and dad forget about us.

06:54.915 --> 06:55.947
That's why they didn't tell us

06:55.949 --> 06:57.282
that they cancelled
Eddie's party.

06:58.685 --> 07:00.552
I'm sick of being a good boy.

07:00.554 --> 07:02.254
[ Gasps ]

07:03.424 --> 07:04.723
I'm sorry, can-do.

07:04.725 --> 07:07.025
Why do I always hurt
the ones I love?

07:07.027 --> 07:08.794
Maybe we should start being bad.

07:08.796 --> 07:10.929
Get some attention.
It works for Eddie.

07:10.931 --> 07:13.365
Yeah!
Let's ask mom if it's okay.

07:13.367 --> 07:15.333
[ Sighs ]

07:17.070 --> 07:19.471
Usher: Thank you.
Enjoy the movie.

07:19.473 --> 07:22.407
Do you remember
where we parked the car?

07:22.409 --> 07:25.577
No, I was too busy
doing my taxes.

07:25.579 --> 07:27.946
I've been thinking
about the war I was in.

07:30.784 --> 07:34.886
Two adults for "Ace ventura:
When nature calls,"

07:34.888 --> 07:36.988
rated pg-13.

07:39.726 --> 07:42.260
Theater 3, to your left.

07:42.262 --> 07:44.963
Thank you, son.
Stay off drugs.

07:46.567 --> 07:48.600
And then we walked
into foot locker,

07:48.602 --> 07:50.669
and we looked at the new
air Jordans for a while.

07:50.671 --> 07:52.771
Brian tried to touch them,
but they wouldn't let him.

07:52.773 --> 07:54.473
Mm. That was it.

07:54.475 --> 07:55.974
Sounds pretty "chill."

07:55.976 --> 07:57.342
'Twas, 'twas.

07:59.246 --> 08:01.246
Evan and I saw a movie today.

08:01.248 --> 08:03.582
A pg-13 movie.

08:03.584 --> 08:04.883
Pass the beans.

08:10.257 --> 08:13.191
It was unsuitable
for ages<i> under</i> 13.

08:14.528 --> 08:17.195
Jim carrey came out
of a rhino's butthole.

08:17.197 --> 08:19.397
Mm.
